Influence of peritoneal lavage on objective prognostic signs in acute pancreatitis. In 39 patients with severe attacks of acute pancreatitis, a longitudinal study was done with respect to the influence of peritoneal lavage on objective prognostic signs (WBC, blood-glucose, serum-calcium, hematocrit, serum-creatinine, arterial pO2, base deficit) amylase activities in peritoneal fluid, serum, and urine